MASTERS TOURNAMENT
April 12, 2015
Hideki Matsuyama
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q.   (No Microphone.)  
HIDEKI MATSUYAMA:   With that said, I have a lot of work left to do still.  
   
 Q.   Four round under par for you.   That's the first time you've done that at the Masters.   
HIDEKI MATSUYAMA:   I really played well this week and I'm happy with the way I played and so I have no complaints.   
   
 Q.   Can you talk us through 13, where you got that eagle?  
HIDEKI MATSUYAMA:   I hit my drive in the pine straw to the right, I had 211 to the pin, and I cut a 5‑iron in there.   It was probably a 10‑footer, 11‑footer.   And I was able to make it.  
   
 Q.   Was that 5‑iron the shot of your tournament?  
HIDEKI MATSUYAMA:   It was one of them, yeah.   
   
 Q.   In your mind, do you feel like you're a Masters champion of the future?  
HIDEKI MATSUYAMA:   I would really like to become a Masters champion some day.   
   
 Q.   Can you give us some idea of what the response has been at home in Japan, as far as you know, this week?  
HIDEKI MATSUYAMA:   (No response.)  
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT